(53, 'FORAGRES WET DIAMOND DRILL BIT 20MM', '4970', 39, 48, 5, '<ul>\r\n	<li>FORAGRES diamond drill bits are ideal for drilling stoneware tiles, porcelain tiles and pieces of granite and marble.</li>\r\n	<li>Available in various diameters, from 20 to 120 mm. They are perfect for making holes in ceramic tiles during installation.</li>\r\n	<li>The FORAGRES range of diamond drill bits includes all the diameters needed to perform the most common drilling for water tapping points, sewers, electrical connections, etc.</li>\r\n	<li>The diamond rim of FORAGRES drill bits is sintered and joined to the drill bit body by laser welding.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>FORAGRES diamond drill bits are ideal for drilling stoneware tiles, porcelain tiles and pieces of granite and marble.</li>\r\n	<li>Available in various diameters, from 20 to 120 mm. They are perfect for making holes in ceramic tiles during installation.</li>\r\n	<li>The FORAGRES range of diamond drill bits includes all the diameters needed to perform the most common drilling for water tapping points, sewers, electrical connections, etc.</li>\r\n	<li>The diamond rim of FORAGRES drill bits is sintered and joined to the drill bit body by laser welding.</li>\r\n	<li>FORAGRES diamond drill bits must ALWAYS be used water-cooled and with a non-percussive power drill.</li>\r\n	<li>The use of the MULTIDRILL centring guide (ref. 50944) is recommended for centring holes with a diameter of up to 83 mm.</li>\r\n	<li>For drilling holes with a diameter greater than 84 mm, the FORAGRES guide is recommended (ref. 50900).</li>\r\n	<li>The average life of the FORAGRES diamond drill bits is 60 holes and ALWAYS depends on the type of material, its thickness and proper cooling and use.</li>\r\n	<li>The drilling depth of the FORAGRES diamond drill bits is 30 mm (33 mm for diameters of 55 and 75 mm).</li>\r\n	<li>The maximum speed of use for FORAGRES diamond drill bits is 900 rpm except in diameters of 100 and 120 mm where the maximum 